---
// LensPanel — the Somnary Lens island (CHK-7.2 + CHK-7.4). The user-facing surface for the Lens engine:
// one free-text prompt (a product name, an ingredient, or a pasted supplement-facts panel) → POST
// /api/lens → the SERVER-composed LensAssessment, rendered by the shared, framework-free renderLensCard
// (the SAFETY-CRITICAL textContent-only renderer). Mirrors GuidePanel / AskPanel: an SSG-safe shell + a
// progressive-enhancement <script> island, token-only styling, aria-live status, reduced-motion.
//
// THE INVARIANT CONTINUES INTO THE UI: this island renders ONLY server-authored fields (via the card
// renderer's textContent-only path). It authors no medical prose — the verdict, evidence, doesNotShow,
// the resolved "read X as Y" line, label flags, safety note, stamp, and disclaimer all come from the
// server. The only strings this file introduces are STRUCTURAL: the input affordances, the example
// seeds, the REAL streamed pipeline-stage labels, and the neutral error registers. No grade is rendered.
//
// LIVE SSE PROGRESS (CHK-7.4): the request asks for text/event-stream; the engine streams REAL pipeline
// milestones (resolving → the interpreted entity, N sources read, verifying, composing) which the island
// shows as they happen — counts shown are the engine's real ones, never fabricated. On the final `done`
// frame the same renderLensCard takes over. A non-streaming fallback (plain JSON) is handled too.
---

<section class="lens" aria-label="Somnary Lens" data-lens>
  <p class="lens-label"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> Somnary Lens</p>
  <p class="prompt">
    Name any sleep product or ingredient — a brand the tier board doesn’t cover, an unfamiliar
    supplement, or paste a supplement-facts panel. The Lens researches the published evidence and shows
    what it does — and doesn’t — establish. It is not a Somnary grade.
  </p>

  <form class="field" data-lens-form>
    <label class="sr-only" for="lens-input">A product, an ingredient, or a pasted label</label>
    <textarea
      id="lens-input"
      class="lens-input"
      name="input"
      rows="3"
      maxlength="4000"
      autocomplete="off"
      placeholder="e.g. Restavit, apigenin, or paste a sleep-gummy supplement-facts panel…"
      data-lens-input></textarea>
    <button type="submit" class="send" data-lens-send>Research this →</button>
  </form>

  <!-- example seeds (STRUCTURAL — click to research; never a recommendation, just starting points) -->
  <div class="examples" data-lens-examples>
    <span class="ex-label">Try:</span>
    <button type="button" class="chip" data-example="Restavit">Restavit</button>
    <button type="button" class="chip" data-example="apigenin">apigenin</button>
    <button type="button" class="chip" data-example="ZzzQuil">ZzzQuil</button>
    <button type="button" class="chip" data-example="magnesium glycinate">magnesium glycinate</button>
    <button type="button" class="chip" data-example="tart cherry">tart cherry</button>
  </div>

  <!-- live SSE progress (REAL pipeline milestones; counts are the engine's real ones) -->
  <div class="progress" data-lens-progress hidden aria-live="polite">
    <p class="p-resolved" data-lens-resolved hidden></p>
    <p class="p-stage" data-lens-stage></p>
    <div class="p-track" aria-hidden="true"><span class="p-bar" data-lens-bar></span></div>
  </div>

  <!-- the server-composed card renders here (textContent-only, via renderLensCard) -->
  <div class="card-region" data-lens-card aria-live="polite" tabindex="-1"></div>

  <!-- Minimal privacy disclosure (server-rendered, static, visible JS-off) — the two verbose blocks
       were retired per owner, but the third-party-AI + "don't share personal details" disclosure is a
       CLAUDE.md non-negotiable, so it stays as one quiet line. -->
  <p class="privacy-line">
    Sent to a third-party AI service (OpenRouter → DeepSeek, Gemini fallback) and to PubMed for sources.
    Don’t include personal or identifying details. <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .lens {
    background: var(--primary-soft);
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    padding: var(--sp-6);
    margin-top: var(--sp-7);
  }
  .sr-only {
    position: absolute;
    width: 1px;
    height: 1px;
    padding: 0;
    margin: -1px;
    overflow: hidden;
